<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-975-090  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 975 090.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Dec 18 1989 v6 n50 p50(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T, MCI plan to interconnect E-mail services. (ATandamp;T Mail; MCICommunications Corp. MCI Mail)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (services)MCI Communications Corp. (services).andO;Ticker:    T; MCIC.andO;Topic:     Electronic mail systemsInteroperabilityAT and T Mail (Electronic mail system)MCI Mail (Electronic mail system)Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Relief is on the way for electronic-mail users who have been frustrated bytheir inability to exchange ATandamp;T Mail and MCI Mail messages: ATandamp;T and MCICommunications Corp. plan to interconnect their commercial E-mail services byFebruary, officials from the companies announced recently.andM;The move will for the first time allow users of the popular services toexchange messages, according to spokespeople for the companies.andM;ATandamp;T Mail, with more than 40,000 subscribers, and MCI Mail, with itssubscriber base of more than 110,000, will be linked using the internationalX.400 standard, which addresses the way in which dissimilar electronic-mailsystems should be connected, according to officials from the two companies.andM;The X.400 messaging specification, which is recommended by the internationalCCITT data-communications standards-setting body, defines guidelines for theformatting, delivery and receipt of electronic messages.andM;Prices for message delivery between the two systems have yet to be announced,company officials said.andM;Neither electronic-mail provider is a stranger to X.400.andP;  MCI has alreadyestablished X.400 interconnections between Dialcom Inc.'s Dialcom, TelenetCommunications Corp.'s Telemail, IBM's Information Network and Italy'snational PT Postel services.andM;ATandamp;T, meanwhile, has joined forces with 11 other services this year,including seven foreign services and, domestically, Dialcom, Telemail andWestern Union Corp.'s EasyLink.andM;ATandamp;T, of Morristown, N.J., can be reached at (201) 898-3842; MCI, ofWashington, can be reached at (914) 934-6480.andO;</TEXT></DOC>